snippet.textDisplay:
Not so easy. None of this was on the cards when they married. The reason(s) why - Wills and Harry fell out - why Kate doesn't like Meghan - why the "Fab Four" and their plans to run a joint trust went bang - why Harry and Megs moved to Frogmore, then spoke of S. Africa, now it's Canada, always further and further from Wills and Kate - in S. Africa Harry told us he was very depressed, the "state of the world" was on his shoulders - none of this was in the pipeline when they married. What WAS in the pipeline was - Meghan wrote a letter to her father, the letter that the Mail on Sunday (MoS) published (edited) and Harry and Megs are sueing the MoS, claiming privacy (maybe) and breach of copyright.


They may well lose. Privacy - Meghan briefed some "friends" (contacts) with "People" magazine and so the public learned of this letter and some contents from Meghan Markle herself via reports in People magazine. Copyright - her father gave the letter to MoS (taking no payment) saying it contains falsehoods by Meghan Markle about Markle Senior. MoS claims public interest if Meghan Markle is spreading falsies about the relationship/the past between her and her father. This will be tested in court unless Harry and Megs withdraw their case. If they do withdraw it, it will say publicly that Meghan Markle lied in her letter and tried to smear her father in the public eye. This makes it very clear that she lied to Harry in telling him of her difficult past. If they continue and lose, it confirms much the same thing. The MoS says it will defend its right to publish "in the public interest" with vigour. It's obvious how this will play - if the hearings are "behind closed doors" and the MoS wins, it will re-publish as "in the public interest" -


"Meghan Markle suckered Harry into the marriage, she's a gold-digger".


It looks as though this is true. The letter was clearly written with Public Relations intent and it's existence was deliberately made public in media before the MoS published. It accuses Markle Senior of hurtful behaviour with the intent of making this a public story. His giving the letter to a newspaper was clearly unexpected but Markle Senior had had enough.


Harry said he didn't like Wills advising him not to marry in haste. Harry did marry quite quickly. None of the royals had much chance to get to know Meghan Markle before the engagement was announced and Harry's military friends all "vanished". What they find is that Meghan Markle has blanked her father and planted this letter/story and it's not good for two reasons


1) If she is adjusting her back-story to the royals, how much bullshit has she fed Harry in "reeling him in", how much does she have to "adjust" that, how much of a liar is she? What now of reports that she moves on and leaves people behind? Do they all report an entirely different "story" from Meghan Markle (as do her family) about her broken past?


2) Harry doesn't know what his wife is doing from one moment to the next and having this next door (or anywhere near) Wills and Kate is out of the question. Leave they must - what will we say?


Crunch time, the royal family has not been in "save Harry and Megs" mode, it's been in survival. A threat of Harry-and-Megs-tell-all on "Oprah's sofa" appears via a journalist - unlikely - both Harry and Meghan would get well trashed and gain nothing.


Meghan Markle has somewhat ballsed it up. So far, Harry is stuck with it and there is now Archie. Remains to be seen how long that may last but it's absolutely clear that Meghan Markle cannot be in the royal family now or at any time in the future. Quite apart from being so objectionable personally, it's a real security risk. So......'arry.....don't think much of yours. Best of luck with that one, pal!


lmfao.
